summary: I don’t know how to describe the feeling I’m feeling waiting for Endgame, but it’s the same as the feeling I had waiting for...
body:
I don’t know how to describe the feeling I’m feeling waiting for Endgame, but it’s the same as the feeling I had waiting for Deathly Hallows Part 2. 

If you asked me to describe my teen years it’d just be “Harry Potter”. I walked out of the last movie feeling empty and like a part of my life was gone and that’s that’s how I feel about Endgame and my 20′s.

I know Marvel will continue to release stuff after Endgame but this is the end of the franchise as we know it. We don’t know who’s going to make it out at the end of this movie (I’m not ready for Tony or Steve to go yet, I’m just not.) I could really tell you my last 11 years in relation to which Marvel movie had just come out.

It’s stupid and I’m really drunk but I just don’t know how to prepare for Endgame, and it’s stupid that I’m this upset about a movie.

title: Shot at the night.
body:
Summary: You love your job and now you must work hard to keep it, but how would you know that to do that, you had to teach the insufferable Bucky barnes?

Pairing: Bucky Barnes x reader. Modern day AU.

Based on the prompt “I’m in love with you, asshole!” for @coffee-with-bucky ​‘s writing challenge. The title is The Killers’ song, and as I was trying to decide what to call this series, it hit me that the theme is a little bit similar to this, idek.

Series

  • Part 1 (Sunday, 2/17/19)
  • Part 2 (Sunday, 2/24/19)
  • Part 3 (Tuesday, 4/16/19)

title: Tom Holland May Have Spoiled Avengers: Endgame Last April
body:
Tom Holland May Have Spoiled Avengers: Endgame Last April

Last year during the press tour for Avengers: Infinity War, Marvel famously paired up Benedict Cumberbatch with Tom Holland to stop him from spoiling the movie. The result was a great video someone did that compiled all the time that Cumberbatch had to stop Holland from saying something in an interview. It looks like it may have missed one time though.

An interview with Access was discovered…

title: New ‘Avengers: Endgame’ theory says one of our favorite heroes knew about the snap all along
body:
New ‘Avengers: Endgame’ theory says one of our favorite heroes knew about the snap all along… OMG!!

Avengers: Endgame will be a movie about the remaining heroes trying to undo the snap and restore order to the universe. We already know as much, although we don’t know exactly how it’ll happen. We also know that they will win no matter how much it hurts us to witness their sacrifices — there’s no question about it, considering that we’re looking at the one future Doctor Strange saw where Thanos…
